    "title" : "QuarkusMainTest with H2 Database",
    "body" : "<p>I'm trying to test an application running with a Quarkus main method annotated with <code>@QuarkusMain</code>. For test reasons I annotated my test class with <code>@QuarkusMainTest</code> which works fine so far. Now that I implemented a storing of data into a database I need to enrich the test with database look-ups. No matter how I try, I always get the error</p>\n<pre><code>java.lang.IllegalStateException: This method is normally automatically overridden in subclasses: did you forget to annotate your entity with @Entity?\n     at io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.common.runtime.AbstractJpaOperations.implementationInjectionMissing(AbstractJpaOperations.java:452)\n     at io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntityBase.listAll(PanacheEntityBase.java:419)\n</code></pre>\n<p>In another test class annotated with <code>@QuarkusTest</code> the same code works fine.</p>\n<p>Since I'm using the <code>quarkus-test-h2</code> dependency for database tests, I also tried to annotate the test class with <code>@QuarkusTestResource(H2DatabaseTestResource.class)</code> without any effect.</p>\n<p>Any idea for the solution?</p>\n<p>My H2 configuration:</p>\n<pre><code>quarkus:\n  datasource:\n    db-kind: h2\n    jdbc:\n      url: 'jdbc:h2:mem:default'\n      driver: 'org.h2.Driver'\n    username: sa\n    password:\n</code></pre>\n",
